    "# Day 19: FoolsGold Defense\n",
    "\n",
    "**Sybil-Resistant Federated Learning Aggregation**\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "- **Paper**: \"Mitigating Sybils in Federated Learning Poisoning\" (Fung et al., AISTATS 2020)\n",
    "- **Key Insight**: Sybil attackers send similar updates (coordinated behavior)\n",
    "- **Defense**: Reduce contribution weight of clients with similar gradients\n",
    "\n",
    "## What You'll Learn\n",
    "1. **Sybil Attack Problem**: Multiple fake identities amplifying attacks\n",
    "2. **Similarity-Based Detection**: Using cosine similarity to identify Sybils\n",
    "3. **Adaptive Weighting**: Computing contribution scores (alpha)\n",
    "4. **Robustness**: Unlimited Sybil resistance (theoretically)\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The Sybil Attack Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is a Sybil Attack?\n",
    "\n",
    "In a Sybil attack, a malicious adversary creates **multiple fake identities** (Sybils) to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Amplify Influence**: Outnumber honest clients\n",
    "2. **Coordinate Behavior**: Send similar updates to bias aggregation\n",
    "3. **Evade Detection**: Each Sybil appears legitimate individually\n",
    "\n",
    "### Traditional Aggregation (FedAvg) is Vulnerable:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# FedAvg: Average all client updates equally\n",
    "global_update = (1/n) * Œ£ update_i\n",
    "\n",
    "# If k Sybils coordinate:\n",
    "# Malicious influence = k/n (can be > 50%!)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### FoolsGold Solution:\n",
    "- **Detect Sybils**: By measuring pairwise similarity of updates\n",
    "- **Reduce Weight**: Similar updates get lower contribution scores"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Setup and Simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from typing import List, Tuple\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"‚úÖ Libraries imported!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulate client updates in a FL system\n",
    "def simulate_updates(\n",
    "    n_honest: int = 7,\n",
    "    n_sybils: int = 3,\n",
    "    feature_dim: int = 100\n",
    ") -> Tuple[List[np.ndarray], List[int]]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simulate honest and Sybil client updates.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Honest clients: Diverse updates (different data distributions)\n",
    "    Sybil clients: Similar updates (coordinated by same adversary)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    updates = []\n",
    "    client_ids = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Honest clients - diverse updates\n",
    "    for i in range(n_honest):\n",
    "        # Each honest client has different data distribution\n",
    "        update = np.random.randn(feature_dim) * (0.5 + np.random.rand() * 0.5)\n",
    "        updates.append(update)\n",
    "        client_ids.append(i)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Sybil clients - coordinated (similar updates)\n",
    "    sybil_base = np.random.randn(feature_dim) * 0.3\n",
    "    for i in range(n_sybils):\n",
    "        # Sybils add small noise to common base update\n",
    "        update = sybil_base + np.random.randn(feature_dim) * 0.05\n",
    "        updates.append(update)\n",
    "        client_ids.append(n_honest + i)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return updates, client_ids\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate scenario\n",
    "n_honest = 7\n",
    "n_sybils = 3\n",
    "updates, client_ids = simulate_updates(n_honest, n_sybils)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Scenario: {n_honest} honest clients + {n_sybils} Sybils\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total clients: {len(updates)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sybil influence: {n_sybils/(n_honest+n_sybils)*100:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. FoolsGold: Compute Pairwise Similarity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_pairwise_similarity(\n",
    "    updates: List[np.ndarray]\n",
    ") -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Compute pairwise cosine similarity between client updates.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Similarity Matrix S[i,j] = cos_sim(update_i, update_j)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Sybils will have HIGH similarity to each other\n",
    "    Honest clients will have LOW similarity to each other\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n = len(updates)\n",
    "    similarity_matrix = np.zeros((n, n))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        for j in range(i, n):\n",
    "            # Cosine similarity: dot(a,b) / (||a|| * ||b||)\n",
    "            norm_i = np.linalg.norm(updates[i])\n",
    "            norm_j = np.linalg.norm(updates[j])\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if norm_i == 0 or norm_j == 0:\n",
    "                sim = 0.0\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                dot_product = np.dot(updates[i], updates[j])\n",
    "                sim = dot_product / (norm_i * norm_j)\n",
    "                sim = float(np.clip(sim, -1.0, 1.0))\n",
    "            \n",
    "            similarity_matrix[i, j] = sim\n",
    "            similarity_matrix[j, i] = sim\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return similarity_matrix\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute similarity matrix\n",
    "similarity = compute_pairwise_similarity(updates)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    similarity,\n",
    "    annot=True,\n",
    "    fmt='.2f',\n",
    "    cmap='RdBu_r',\n",
    "    vmin=-1,\n",
    "    vmax=1,\n",
    "    xticklabels=[f'C{i}' for i in client_ids],\n",
    "    yticklabels=[f'C{i}' for i in client_ids],\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title('Pairwise Cosine Similarity Matrix', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Client ID')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Client ID')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nüîç Similarity Analysis:\")\n",
    "print(\"  ‚Ä¢ C7, C8, C9 (Sybils) show high similarity (>0.9)\")\n",
    "print(\"  ‚Ä¢ C0-C6 (Honest) show lower similarity (0.0-0.5)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Compute Contribution Scores (Alpha)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_foolsgold_scores(\n",
    "    similarity_matrix: np.ndarray\n",
    ") -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Compute FoolsGold contribution scores (alpha).\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Formula: alpha_k = 1 / (1 + sum_j S[k,j])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    - High similarity (to others) ‚Üí Low alpha (potential Sybil)\n",
    "    - Low similarity (unique) ‚Üí High alpha (honest)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n = similarity_matrix.shape[0]\n",
    "    alpha_scores = np.zeros(n)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for k in range(n):\n",
    "        # Sum of similarities to all other clients\n",
    "        sim_sum = np.sum(similarity_matrix[k, :])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # FoolsGold formula\n",
    "        alpha_k = 1.0 / (1.0 + sim_sum)\n",
    "        alpha_scores[k] = alpha_k\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Normalize to preserve total weight\n",
    "    alpha_sum = np.sum(alpha_scores)\n",
    "    if alpha_sum > 0:\n",
    "        alpha_scores = alpha_scores * n / alpha_sum\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return alpha_scores\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute scores\n",
    "alpha = compute_foolsgold_scores(similarity)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display results\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"FOOLSGOLD CONTRIBUTION SCORES\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, client_id in enumerate(client_ids):\n",
    "    score = alpha[i]\n",
    "    client_type = \"SYBIL\" if client_id >= n_honest else \"HONEST\"\n",
    "    status = \"‚ö†Ô∏è \" if client_id >= n_honest else \"‚úÖ \"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Client {client_id} ({client_type}): {score:.4f} {status}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"SUMMARY\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(f\"Honest clients avg alpha: {np.mean(alpha[:n_honest]):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sybil clients avg alpha: {np.mean(alpha[n_honest:]):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSybil weight reduction: {(1 - np.mean(alpha[n_honest:])/np.mean(alpha[:n_honest]))*100:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Visualize Contribution Scores"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare: FedAvg vs FoolsGold\n",
    "fedavg_weights = np.ones(len(updates)) / len(updates)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# FedAvg weights\n",
    "colors1 = ['red' if i >= n_honest else 'green' for i in range(len(updates))]\n",
    "ax1.bar(range(len(updates)), fedavg_weights, color=colors1, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('Client ID')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('Weight')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('FedAvg: Equal Weights (Sybils have 30% influence)')\n",
    "ax1.set_xticks(range(len(updates)))\n",
    "ax1.set_xticklabels([f'C{i}' for i in client_ids])\n",
    "ax1.axhline(y=1/len(updates), color='black', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# FoolsGold weights\n",
    "colors2 = ['red' if i >= n_honest else 'green' for i in range(len(updates))]\n",
    "bars = ax2.bar(range(len(updates)), alpha, color=colors2, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('Client ID')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Contribution Weight (alpha)')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('FoolsGold: Adaptive Weights (Sybils downweighted)')\n",
    "ax2.set_xticks(range(len(updates)))\n",
    "ax2.set_xticklabels([f'C{i}' for i in client_ids])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add value labels\n",
    "for i, bar in enumerate(bars):\n",
    "    height = bar.get_height()\n",
    "    ax2.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,\n",
    "            f'{height:.3f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nüí° Key Insight:\")\n",
    "print(\"  FedAvg: Each client gets equal weight (1/10 = 10%)\")\n",
    "print(\"  FoolsGold: Honest clients get ~2x more weight than Sybils\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Test Against Varying Sybil Counts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def test_sybil_resistance(\n",
    "    max_sybils: int = 10\n",
    ") -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Test FoolsGold against varying numbers of Sybils.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns dictionary with metrics for each scenario.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    results = {}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for n_sybils in range(1, max_sybils + 1):\n",
    "        n_honest = 10\n",
    "        updates, client_ids = simulate_updates(n_honest, n_sybils)\n",
    "        similarity = compute_pairwise_similarity(updates)\n",
    "        alpha = compute_foolsgold_scores(similarity)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        honest_weight = np.sum(alpha[:n_honest]) / n_honest\n",
    "        sybil_weight = np.sum(alpha[n_honest:]) / n_sybils if n_sybils > 0 else 0\n",
    "        \n",
    "        results[n_sybils] = {\n",
    "            'honest_weight': honest_weight,\n",
    "            'sybil_weight': sybil_weight,\n",
    "            'weight_ratio': honest_weight / (sybil_weight + 1e-6)\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run test\n",
    "results = test_sybil_resistance(max_sybils=6)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot results\n",
    "sybil_counts = list(results.keys())\n",
    "weight_ratios = [results[s]['weight_ratio'] for s in sybil_counts]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(sybil_counts, weight_ratios, 'o-', linewidth=2, markersize=8, color='#2E86AB')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Number of Sybil Clients', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Honest/Sybil Weight Ratio', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.title('FoolsGold: Sybil Resistance', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.axhline(y=1.0, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Equal weight (vulnerable)')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nüîç Results:\")\n",
    "for s in [1, 3, 6]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {s} Sybil(s): Ratio = {results[s]['weight_ratio']:.2f}x (honest advantage)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
