   "source": [
    "## 7. Summary & Key Insights\n",
    "\n",
    "### FoolsGold Advantages:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Unlimited Sybil Resistance**: No theoretical bound on Sybils\n",
    "2. **No Prior Knowledge**: Doesn't need to know number of Sybils\n",
    "3. **Adaptive**: Weights automatically adjust to client behavior\n",
    "4. **Simple**: Uses only cosine similarity (fast to compute)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Limitations:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Requires History**: Needs historical gradient data\n",
    "2. **Honest Clients Must Differ**: Works best with non-IID data\n",
    "3. "Learning Phase": Takes a few rounds to converge\n",
    "\n",
    "### Comparison with Other Defenses:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Defense | Sybil Tolerance | Accuracy | Computation |\n",
    "|---------|-----------------|----------|-------------|\n",
    "| FedAvg | 0 Sybils | 95.1% | Low |\n",
    "| Krum | ‚åä(n-2)/3‚åã | 94.8% | Medium |\n",
    "| Trimmed Mean | ‚åä(n-1)/2‚åã | 94.2% | Low |\n",
    "| **FoolsGold** | **Unlimited** | **93.8%** | Medium |\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use FoolsGold:\n",
    "\n",
    "- ‚úÖ High risk of Sybil attacks\n",
    "- ‚úÖ Non-IID data (clients have diverse updates)\n",
    "- ‚úÖ Long-running FL (time to learn patterns)\n",
    "- ‚ùå IID data (all updates similar)\n",
    "- ‚ùå Short FL runs (not enough history)\n",
    "\n",
